;Participation Guidelines
Miongozo Ya Kushiriki


;The Mozilla Festival respects Mozilla’s community participation guidelines. These guidelines cover our behaviour as participants, facilitators, wranglers, staff, volunteers, vendors, and anyone else involved in making MozFest possible.
Tamasha la Mozilla linaheshimu miongozo ya kushiriki ya jamii ya Mozilla. Miongozo hii inahusu tabia yetu kama washiriki, wasaidizi, viongozi, wafanyakazi, wanaojitolea, wachuuzi, na mtu mwingine yeyote anayehusika katika ufanisi wa MozFest.


;How to treat each other:
Jinsi ya kujihusisha na wengine:


;Be respectful and value each other’s ideas, styles and viewpoints.
Kuwa mwenye heshima na kutilia maanani dhana, mitindo na maoni ya kila mmoja.


;Be direct but professional; we cannot withhold hard truths.
Peana maoni yako lakini kwa utaalamu; tusijiwekee ukweli ulio wazi.


;Be inclusive and help new perspectives be heard.
Wahusishe wote na uyasaidie maoni mapya kusikika.


;Appreciate and accommodate our many cultural practices, attitudes and beliefs.
Tilia maanani na uzipe nafasi tamaduni, mitazamo na imani ya watu mbali mbali.


;Be open to learning from others.
Kubali kujifunza kutoka watu wengine.


;Lead by example and match your actions with your words.
Ongoza kwa mfano na matendo yako yawe sawa na maneno yako.


;The following will not be tolerated at MozFest: violence and threats of violence; personal attacks; derogatory language; unwelcome sexual attention or physical contact; disruptive behaviour; influencing unacceptable behaviour.
Mambo haya hayataruhusiwa katika MozFest: vurugu au vitisho; kumuonea mtu binafsi; lugha chafu; kutongozana au uhusiano wa kimapenzi wa aina yoyote ile; tabia za kujaribu kukatiza shughuli; kusababisha mambo yasiyo kubalika.


;Are you seeing behaviour that doesn’t respect these guidelines? Email festival@mozilla.org or call +44 20 7855 3030
Je, umeziona tabia zisizo yaheshimu maagizo haya? Tuma barua pepe kwa festival@mozilla.org au piga simu +44 20 7855 3030


